#: 01N0301
msgid "No way!"
msgstr "No way!"

#: 01N0302
msgid "Wow! I've never seen one like this before. It looks just like Studly, only smaller."
msgstr "Wow! I've never seen one like this before. It looks just like Studly, only smaller."

#: 01N0303
msgid "Ah! Not so fast, Wilbur! His head's floppy!"
msgstr "Ah! Not so fast, Wilbur! His head's floppy!"

#: 01N0304
msgid "I mean, it's broken. There's no spring in it, so his head's flopping all over the place. No trade."
msgstr "I mean, it's broken. There's no spring in it, so his head's flopping all over the place. No trade."

#: 01N0401
msgid "It's also very broken. Take a hike, Wilbur!"
msgstr "It's also very broken. Take a hike, Wilbur!"

#: 01N0402
msgid "You fix it, then we'll talk, grasshoppers!"
msgstr "You fix it, then we'll talk, grasshoppers!"

#: 01N0403
msgid "You're welcome."
msgstr "You're welcome."

#: 01N0501
msgid "Hey, who are you trying to fool? It's still broken!"
msgstr "Hey, who are you trying to fool? It's still broken!"

#: 01N0701
msgid "Let me see it!"
msgstr "Let me see it!"

#: 01N0702
msgid "Hey, it works great!"
msgstr "Hey, it works great!"

#: 01N0801
msgid "No way!"
msgstr "No way!"

#: 01N0802
msgid "Wow! I've never seen one like this before. It looks just like Studly, only smaller."
msgstr "Wow! I've never seen one like this before. It looks just like Studly, only smaller."

#: 01N0901
msgid "Okay, Wilbur. It's a trade. They're in the icebox outside Verus. Go help yourself."
msgstr "Okay, Wilbur. It's a trade. They're in the icebox outside Verus. Go help yourself."

#: 01N1001
msgid "I can't give you these grasshoppers, I'm using them!"
msgstr "I can't give you these grasshoppers, I'm using them!"

#: 01N1002
msgid "Duh! To keep them frozen!"
msgstr "Duh! To keep them frozen!"

#: 01N1003
msgid "They are fresh, Wilbur. They'll start hopping around like crazy once you thaw them out."
msgstr "They are fresh, Wilbur. They'll start hopping around like crazy once you thaw them out."

#: 01N1004
msgid "Why use my mom's microwave? Well, when she's not looking."
msgstr "Why use my mom's microwave? Well, when she's not looking."

#: 01N1005
msgid "Grasshoppers are hard to come by most of the year, except every spring there's tons of them down at the marsh. I catch a year's supply in the spring and keep them on ice so I have fresh bait all year round."
msgstr "Grasshoppers are hard to come by most of the year, except every spring there's tons of them down at the marsh. I catch a year's supply in the spring and keep them on ice so I have fresh bait all year round."

#: 01N1006
msgid "Because my mom says I can't keep them in her freezer."
msgstr "Because my mom says I can't keep them in her freezer."

#: 01N1007
msgid "Hey, no prob! And if you ever need any frisky termites, I can make you a heck of a deal!"
msgstr "Hey, no prob! And if you ever need any frisky termites, I can make you a heck of a deal!"

#: 01N1301
msgid "I don't want that."
msgstr "I don't want that."

#: 01N14011
msgid "What am I supposed to do with that?"
msgstr "What am I supposed to do with that?"

#: 01N14012
msgid "I don't think so."
msgstr "I don't think so."

#: 01N14013
msgid "Stop wasting my time, Wilbur!"
msgstr "Stop wasting my time, Wilbur!"

#: 01N14014
msgid "Can't you see I'm busy?"
msgstr "Can't you see I'm busy?"

#: 01N14015
msgid "Get a life, Wilbur!"
msgstr "Get a life, Wilbur!"

#: 01N14016
msgid "That's nothing but junk, Wilbur!"
msgstr "That's nothing but junk, Wilbur!"

#: 01N15011
msgid "Look, I appreciate the puzzle dispenser, but I don't want anything else."
msgstr "Look, I appreciate the puzzle dispenser, but I don't want anything else."

#: 01N15012
msgid "I don't want that! Go away and let me fish!"
msgstr "I don't want that! Go away and let me fish!"

#: 01N15013
msgid "Leave me alone! I don't want any more of your stuff!"
msgstr "Leave me alone! I don't want any more of your stuff!"

#: 01N1601
msgid "You're welcome."
msgstr "You're welcome."

#: 01N1701
msgid "Hey, no prob! And if you ever need any frisky termites, I can make you a heck of a deal."
msgstr "Hey, no prob! And if you ever need any frisky termites, I can make you a heck of a deal."

#: 01P0301
msgid "Check it out, Odie! A studly McQuark pause dispenser!"
msgstr "Check it out, Odie! A studly McQuark pause dispenser!"

#: 01P0302
msgid "Wait! It's an official limited edition collector's item!"
msgstr "Wait! It's an official limited edition collector's item!"

#: 01P0303
msgid "Give me some grasshoppers, and it's yours!"
msgstr "Give me some grasshoppers, and it's yours!"

#: 01P0304
msgid "What do you mean?"
msgstr "What do you mean?"

#: 01P0401
msgid "But it's very rare!"
msgstr "But it's very rare!"

#: 01P0402
msgid "Hmm... what if I fix it?"
msgstr "Hmm... what if I fix it?"

#: 01P0403
msgid "Thanks for nothing, Odie."
msgstr "Thanks for nothing, Odie."

#: 01P0701
msgid "I fixed the puzzle dispenser, Odie!"
msgstr "I fixed the puzzle dispenser, Odie!"

#: 01P0801
msgid "Check it out, Odie! A studly McQuark Puzz Dispenser!"
msgstr "Check it out, Odie! A studly McQuark Puzz Dispenser!"

#: 01P0802
msgid "By the way, it's an official limited edition collector's item."
msgstr "By the way, it's an official limited edition collector's item."

#: 01P0803
msgid "Well, give me some grasshoppers, and it's yours!"
msgstr "Well, give me some grasshoppers, and it's yours!"

#: 01P1001
msgid "Can I just take some from your bait box?"
msgstr "Can I just take some from your bait box?"

#: 01P1002
msgid "Why are they in an icebox?"
msgstr "Why are they in an icebox?"

#: 01P1003
msgid "I thought you said your bait was fresh."
msgstr "I thought you said your bait was fresh."

#: 01P1004
msgid "Well, how do you saw him out?"
msgstr "Well, how do you saw him out?"

#: 01P1005
msgid "Why do you keep them frozen?"
msgstr "Why do you keep them frozen?"

#: 01P1006
msgid "Why do you keep them at Verus?"
msgstr "Why do you keep them at Verus?"

#: 01P1007
msgid "Thanks, kid."
msgstr "Thanks, kid."

#: 01P1101
msgid "I'll trade you this for some grasshoppers."
msgstr "I'll trade you this for some grasshoppers."

#: 01P1601
msgid "Thanks for nothing, Odie."
msgstr "Thanks for nothing, Odie."

#: 01P1701
msgid "Thanks, kid."
msgstr "Thanks, kid."

#: 02N0301
msgid "Trying to steal from a kid? Nice, Wilbur."
msgstr "Trying to steal from a kid? Nice, Wilbur."

#: 02N04011
msgid "Nice try, Wilbur."
msgstr "Nice try, Wilbur."

#: 02N04012
msgid "Pick on someone your own size, Wilbur!"
msgstr "Pick on someone your own size, Wilbur!"

#: 02N04013
msgid "Get your paws off my bait!"
msgstr "Get your paws off my bait!"

#: 02N04014
msgid "You're starting to bug me, Wilbur!"
msgstr "You're starting to bug me, Wilbur!"

#: 02N04015
msgid "You don't give up, do ya?"
msgstr "You don't give up, do ya?"

#: 02N04016
msgid "Get lost, will ya? You're scaring the fish!"
msgstr "Get lost, will ya? You're scaring the fish!"

#: 02N0601
msgid "Hey! Hands off! I'm using them! I told you where the frozen ones are, so leave me alone!"
msgstr "Hey! Hands off! I'm using them! I told you where the frozen ones are, so leave me alone!"

#: 02N07011
msgid "Don't you have to meet your little space friends or something, Wilbur?"
msgstr "Don't you have to meet your little space friends or something, Wilbur?"

#: 02N07012
msgid "You try that once more, and I'm screaming for the cops!"
msgstr "You try that once more, and I'm screaming for the cops!"

#: 02N07013
msgid "Don't even think about it!"
msgstr "Don't even think about it!"

#: 03N0201
msgid "They're not!"
msgstr "They're not!"

#: 03N0301
msgid "No way! Big old trout's jumping like crazy, and I'm gonna catch him!"
msgstr "No way! Big old trout's jumping like crazy, and I'm gonna catch him!"

#: 03N0401
msgid "Yep, best fishing spot in the whole of Boonesville."
msgstr "Yep, best fishing spot in the whole of Boonesville."

#: 03N0402
msgid "Harry says this is the exact spot where he caught that big fish on the wall in his barber shop."
msgstr "Harry says this is the exact spot where he caught that big fish on the wall in his barber shop."

#: 03N0403
msgid "It's summer, Wilbur."
msgstr "It's summer, Wilbur."

#: 03N0404
msgid "Fresh bait!"
msgstr "Fresh bait!"

#: 03N0405
msgid "I used to use worms, but I didn't like them. Ugh, too slimy. So, now I use grasshoppers."
msgstr "I used to use worms, but I didn't like them. Ugh, too slimy. So, now I use grasshoppers."

#: 03N0407
msgid "Oh, the new Studly McQuark flick is awesome! I saw it five times already, and that was just on Saturday!"
msgstr "Oh, the new Studly McQuark flick is awesome! I saw it five times already, and that was just on Saturday!"

#: 03N0408
msgid "Oh yeah, I have all his comics, gum cards, and action figures. I'm also a member of the Study McQuark fan club."
msgstr "Oh yeah, I have all his comics, gum cards, and action figures. I'm also a member of the Study McQuark fan club."

#: 03N0409
msgid "Yeah. See ya!"
msgstr "Yeah. See ya!"

#: 03N0501
msgid "Well, sometimes I just don't feel good enough to go to school."
msgstr "Well, sometimes I just don't feel good enough to go to school."

#: 03N0502
msgid "Yeah, isn't that funny? You know what? I bet the fresh air does me good."
msgstr "Yeah, isn't that funny? You know what? I bet the fresh air does me good."

#: 03N0601
msgid "Yep, the trout get one look at them, and they just start to slobberin'."
msgstr "Yep, the trout get one look at them, and they just start to slobberin'."

#: 03N0602
msgid "No, not yet. But last week, I caught an old rubber boot!"
msgstr "No, not yet. But last week, I caught an old rubber boot!"

#: 03N0603
msgid "I don't use no sissy lures!"
msgstr "I don't use no sissy lures!"

#: 03N0604
msgid "No way! They'll hop out of the box, Wilbur! I don't want to lose any!"
msgstr "No way! They'll hop out of the box, Wilbur! I don't want to lose any!"

#: 03N0605
msgid "Yeah, whatever."
msgstr "Yeah, whatever."

#: 03N0606
msgid "Forget it. But, I do know where you can get some."
msgstr "Forget it. But, I do know where you can get some."

#: 03N0607
msgid "Hey, I don't want your money! Say, what do you want with grasshoppers anyway, Wilbur?"
msgstr "Hey, I don't want your money! Say, what do you want with grasshoppers anyway, Wilbur?"

#: 03N0608
msgid "Yeah. See ya!"
msgstr "Yeah. See ya!"

#: 03N0701
msgid "Don't worry. One way or another, that trout will be mine."
msgstr "Don't worry. One way or another, that trout will be mine."

#: 03N0801
msgid "It'll cost you a buck to find out!"
msgstr "It'll cost you a buck to find out!"

#: 03N0802
msgid "Suit yourself!"
msgstr "Suit yourself!"

#: 03N0902
msgid "Suit yourself!"
msgstr "Suit yourself!"

#: 03N1001
msgid "Oh, at the pet store. Where you work?"
msgstr "Oh, at the pet store. Where you work?"

#: 03N1002
msgid "Oh, that's too bad! You really should, you know."
msgstr "Oh, that's too bad! You really should, you know."

#: 03N1101
msgid "In that case, they're definitely not for sale. I don't need any competition."
msgstr "In that case, they're definitely not for sale. I don't need any competition."

#: 03N1102
msgid "Hey, you and Stole even hit in the same bottle?"
msgstr "Hey, you and Stole even hit in the same bottle?"

#: 03N1103
msgid "Yeah? What are you gonna be, the clown? Oh man, Wilbur. You gotta see ol' Doc Hooper. He's starting to sound pretty nutso."
msgstr "Yeah? What are you gonna be, the clown? Oh man, Wilbur. You gotta see ol' Doc Hooper. He's starting to sound pretty nutso."

#: 03N1201
msgid "And if I give you some grasshoppers, will all be saved?"
msgstr "And if I give you some grasshoppers, will all be saved?"

#: 03N1202
msgid "My mom always told me to stay away from you. Now I see why."
msgstr "My mom always told me to stay away from you. Now I see why."

#: 03P0201
msgid "Hi, Odie. How are they biting today?"
msgstr "Hi, Odie. How are they biting today?"

#: 03P0301
msgid "Hey, Odie! Not giving up, huh?"
msgstr "Hey, Odie! Not giving up, huh?"

#: 03P0401
msgid "You fish here every day?"
msgstr "You fish here every day?"

#: 03P0402
msgid "What's so special about this spot?"
msgstr "What's so special about this spot?"

#: 03P0403
msgid "Shouldn't you be in school?"
msgstr "Shouldn't you be in school?"

#: 03P0404
msgid "Hey, what's in the box?"
msgstr "Hey, what's in the box?"

#: 03P0405
msgid "What kind of bait do you use?"
msgstr "What kind of bait do you use?"

#: 03P0406
msgid "About your grasshoppers..."
msgstr "About your grasshoppers..."

#: 03P0407
msgid "Seen any good movies lately?"
msgstr "Seen any good movies lately?"

#: 03P0408
msgid "You must be a big Stanley McQuark fan."
msgstr "You must be a big Stanley McQuark fan."

#: 03P0409
msgid "Well, good luck! I gotta go now!"
msgstr "Well, good luck! I gotta go now!"

#: 03P0501
msgid "Oh yeah, but I've seen you here in the spring and fall, too."
msgstr "Oh yeah, but I've seen you here in the spring and fall, too."

#: 03P0502
msgid "But you feel good enough to fish, huh?"
msgstr "But you feel good enough to fish, huh?"

#: 03P0601
msgid "Well, they sure are lively little suckers."
msgstr "Well, they sure are lively little suckers."

#: 03P0602
msgid "Any bites yet?"
msgstr "Any bites yet?"

#: 03P0603
msgid "Well, maybe you should try using lures instead."
msgstr "Well, maybe you should try using lures instead."

#: 03P0604
msgid "Can I see your grasshoppers?"
msgstr "Can I see your grasshoppers?"

#: 03P0605
msgid "I remember when you were knee-high to one."
msgstr "I remember when you were knee-high to one."

#: 03P0606
msgid "Can I buy some from you?"
msgstr "Can I buy some from you?"

#: 03P0607
msgid "Are you sure they're not for sale?"
msgstr "Are you sure they're not for sale?"

#: 03P0608
msgid "Well, good luck. I gotta go now."
msgstr "Well, good luck. I gotta go now."

#: 03P0701
msgid "A rubber boot? Do you mean you haven't caught any fish here all summer?"
msgstr "A rubber boot? Do you mean you haven't caught any fish here all summer?"

#: 03P0801
msgid "Hey, where can I get some grasshoppers?"
msgstr "Hey, where can I get some grasshoppers?"

#: 03P0802
msgid "Never mind, I don't want any."
msgstr "Never mind, I don't want any."

#: 03P0901
msgid "Well, well, Odie, you drive a hard bargain, but..."
msgstr "Well, well, Odie, you drive a hard bargain, but..."

#: 03P0902
msgid "A dollar? Forget it!"
msgstr "A dollar? Forget it!"

#: 03P1001
msgid "There you go. Now, where can I get some grasshoppers?"
msgstr "There you go. Now, where can I get some grasshoppers?"

#: 03P1002
msgid "But we don't sell grasshoppers."
msgstr "But we don't sell grasshoppers."

#: 03P1101
msgid "Hey, I want to go fishing too."
msgstr "Hey, I want to go fishing too."

#: 03P1102
msgid "I'm gonna be abducted by aliens!"
msgstr "I'm gonna be abducted by aliens!"

#: 03P1103
msgid "I'm starting a miniature grasshopper circus."
msgstr "I'm starting a miniature grasshopper circus."

#: 03P1201
msgid "I'm telling you the truth. They're testing me to see if humans are intelligent. Odie, if I fail these tests, they're gonna eat us!"
msgstr "I'm telling you the truth. They're testing me to see if humans are intelligent. Odie, if I fail these tests, they're gonna eat us!"

#: 03P1202
msgid "Hopefully."
msgstr "Hopefully."

#: 04N0201
msgid "Well, there's always something good on TV. Here, check this out."
msgstr "Well, there's always something good on TV. Here, check this out."

#: 04N0202
msgid "I don't know, more than I can watch, but that don't stop me from trying."
msgstr "I don't know, more than I can watch, but that don't stop me from trying."

#: 04N0203
msgid "I just kind of surf from channel to channel and let it all wash over me. Hey, you know I can get Baywatch in over 80 languages now?"
msgstr "I just kind of surf from channel to channel and let it all wash over me. Hey, you know I can get Baywatch in over 80 languages now?"

#: 04N0204
msgid "You betcha! I got a 96-inch Jumbotron on order from Fast Freddy's Discount Electronics. It has five times the screen area as the one I got now."
msgstr "You betcha! I got a 96-inch Jumbotron on order from Fast Freddy's Discount Electronics. It has five times the screen area as the one I got now."

#: 04N0205
msgid "Well, let me put it this way. I can watch reruns of Charlie's Angels at any time of the day or night now."
msgstr "Well, let me put it this way. I can watch reruns of Charlie's Angels at any time of the day or night now."

#: 04N0206
msgid "Oh, it's working just fine. Well, except for those dang pigeons."
msgstr "Oh, it's working just fine. Well, except for those dang pigeons."

#: 04N0207
msgid "Oh, they keep landing on it and moving it so it points in the wrong direction. Don't really message up my TV reception."
msgstr "Oh, they keep landing on it and moving it so it points in the wrong direction. Don't really message up my TV reception."

#: 04N0208
msgid "Is that so? Well, you just be sure to tell them to keep their flying saucers away from those TV satellites up there. I'm having enough trouble with pigeons mucking with my dish down here."
msgstr "Is that so? Well, you just be sure to tell them to keep their flying saucers away from those TV satellites up there. I'm having enough trouble with pigeons mucking with my dish down here."

#: 04N02091
msgid "Well, step right up."
msgstr "Well, step right up."

#: 04N02092
msgid "I already cut your hair, you fool kid."
msgstr "I already cut your hair, you fool kid."

#: 04N0210
msgid "What do you want to know?"
msgstr "What do you want to know?"

#: 04N0211
msgid "Huh? Oh, well actually, it's been pretty slow lately. You're the only one who's been in here all week."
msgstr "Huh? Oh, well actually, it's been pretty slow lately. You're the only one who's been in here all week."

#: 04N0301
msgid "Ah, you're so young, Wilbur."
msgstr "Ah, you're so young, Wilbur."

#: 04N0401
msgid "It was driving me nuts. I must have been up in that roof at least a dozen times last week, shooing off them birds and re-aiming the dish."
msgstr "It was driving me nuts. I must have been up in that roof at least a dozen times last week, shooing off them birds and re-aiming the dish."

#: 04N0402
msgid "Well, that's because I put a stair-crow up on the roof. Mm-hmm. Birds ain't gone near that dish ever since."
msgstr "Well, that's because I put a stair-crow up on the roof. Mm-hmm. Birds ain't gone near that dish ever since."

#: 04N0403
msgid "Yep, works like a charm. It even scared the wife. She thinks it looks like me."
msgstr "Yep, works like a charm. It even scared the wife. She thinks it looks like me."

#: 04N0404
msgid "Okay Wilbur, don't be a stranger."
msgstr "Okay Wilbur, don't be a stranger."

#: 04N0501
msgid "I was wondering how much longer you was gonna let that mop grow."
msgstr "I was wondering how much longer you was gonna let that mop grow."

#: 04N0502
msgid "Now, how about that piece that keeps falling in your eyes? Want me to snip it?"
msgstr "Now, how about that piece that keeps falling in your eyes? Want me to snip it?"

#: 04N0503
msgid "Kids today, with their long hair and love beads."
msgstr "Kids today, with their long hair and love beads."

#: 04N0601
msgid "Oh, they say it's dangerous. Supposedly, it seeps right into your brain. But you know, even if that is the case, I gotta tell you, that blue concoction is the best dang styling wax I ever used!"
msgstr "Oh, they say it's dangerous. Supposedly, it seeps right into your brain. But you know, even if that is the case, I gotta tell you, that blue concoction is the best dang styling wax I ever used!"

#: 04N0602
msgid "It works miracles, Wilbur. Especially on dry, staticky, fly-away hair like Mayor Gus has. No wonder he don't stop using it, even though it's supposed to be unhealthy and all."
msgstr "It works miracles, Wilbur. Especially on dry, staticky, fly-away hair like Mayor Gus has. No wonder he don't stop using it, even though it's supposed to be unhealthy and all."

#: 04N0603
msgid "Economics, Wilbur. Toxic waste is cheap, cheap, cheap. Them hot dog guys said you can pick up a barrel for a song."
msgstr "Economics, Wilbur. Toxic waste is cheap, cheap, cheap. Them hot dog guys said you can pick up a barrel for a song."

#: 04N0604
msgid "Yeah, it was a hot dog manufacturer that leaked the news to the hair channel. They was mad that the hair wax guys were moving in on their supplier."
msgstr "Yeah, it was a hot dog manufacturer that leaked the news to the hair channel. They was mad that the hair wax guys were moving in on their supplier."

#: 04N0605
msgid "The toxic waste came from the chemical factory over in Sheldonburg. The hair channel correspondent said they're doing some kind of superconductor research up there. Wait a minute... You know, I'll bet that's why the wax works so well on dry, staticky, fly-away hair. That superconductive toxic waste probably just conducts the static electricity away."
msgstr "The toxic waste came from the chemical factory over in Sheldonburg. The hair channel correspondent said they're doing some kind of superconductor research up there. Wait a minute... You know, I'll bet that's why the wax works so well on dry, staticky, fly-away hair. That superconductive toxic waste probably just conducts the static electricity away."

#: 04N0606
msgid "Well, you can thank my satellite dish for that."
msgstr "Well, you can thank my satellite dish for that."

#: 04N0607
msgid "Nah, he was always a few tacos short of a combination plate. But since he's been using that stuff, he says the fillings in his teeth are picking up better radio stations."
msgstr "Nah, he was always a few tacos short of a combination plate. But since he's been using that stuff, he says the fillings in his teeth are picking up better radio stations."

#: 04N0608
msgid "See ya, Robo."
msgstr "See ya, Robo."

#: 04N0701
msgid "Oh, I don't mind. It lets me get caught up in all my soaps."
msgstr "Oh, I don't mind. It lets me get caught up in all my soaps."

#: 04N0702
msgid "Well, I've been meaning to sweep that up. And I will! Just as soon as I get a little bit of free time."
msgstr "Well, I've been meaning to sweep that up. And I will! Just as soon as I get a little bit of free time."

#: 04N0703
msgid "Well, that's because Stolie broke it the other day. Shoot, I caught him red-handed trying to jimmy it open. He said he wanted to see where all the stripes were disappearing to."
msgstr "Well, that's because Stolie broke it the other day. Shoot, I caught him red-handed trying to jimmy it open. He said he wanted to see where all the stripes were disappearing to."

#: 04N0704
msgid "Later, Wilber!"
msgstr "Later, Wilber!"

#: 04P0201
msgid "Anything good on the tube?"
msgstr "Anything good on the tube?"

#: 04P0202
msgid "How many channels do you get now?"
msgstr "How many channels do you get now?"

#: 04P0203
msgid "How do you decide which show to watch?"
msgstr "How do you decide which show to watch?"

#: 04P0204
msgid "Could you possibly watch any more TV?"
msgstr "Could you possibly watch any more TV?"

#: 04P0205
msgid "Sounds like you're pretty happy with your dish."
msgstr "Sounds like you're pretty happy with your dish."

#: 04P0206
msgid "How's your new satellite dish working?"
msgstr "How's your new satellite dish working?"

#: 04P0207
msgid "What are the pigeons doing to your dish?"
msgstr "What are the pigeons doing to your dish?"

#: 04P0208
msgid "Did I mention that I've been abducted by aliens?"
msgstr "Did I mention that I've been abducted by aliens?"

#: 04P0209
msgid "I'd like a haircut, please."
msgstr "I'd like a haircut, please."

#: 04P0210
msgid "About that toxic hair styling wax..."
msgstr "About that toxic hair styling wax..."

#: 04P0211
msgid "Well, judging by the floor, business must be booming!"
msgstr "Well, judging by the floor, business must be booming!"

#: 04P0301
msgid "Wow! Uh, what is Charlie's Angels?"
msgstr "Wow! Uh, what is Charlie's Angels?"

#: 04P0401
msgid "Sounds like a frustrating problem."
msgstr "Sounds like a frustrating problem."

#: 04P0402
msgid "The dish seems to be working okay now!"
msgstr "The dish seems to be working okay now!"

#: 04P0403
msgid "A scarecrow? That's a clever solution."
msgstr "A scarecrow? That's a clever solution."

#: 04P0404
msgid "Happy channel surfing! I have to go now."
msgstr "Happy channel surfing! I have to go now."

#: 04P0503
msgid "Nope, just a little off the sides, please."
msgstr "Nope, just a little off the sides, please."

#: 04P0601
msgid "Isn't toxic waste a little dangerous?"
msgstr "Isn't toxic waste a little dangerous?"

#: 04P0602
msgid "What's so great about this hair wax?"
msgstr "What's so great about this hair wax?"

#: 04P0603
msgid "Why did they make their hair wax out of toxic waste?"
msgstr "Why did they make their hair wax out of toxic waste?"

#: 04P0604
msgid "Hot dog, guys!"
msgstr "Hot dog, guys!"

#: 04P0605
