msgid "If I pry the gate open, that vicious mongrel will eat me alive!"
msgstr "If I pry the gate open, that vicious mongrel will eat me alive!"

#: 106W015
msgid "Impound Yard!"
msgstr "Impound Yard!"

#: 106W016
msgid "This big tire is just like the one old peg leg eats his lunch out of."
msgstr "This big tire is just like the one old peg leg eats his lunch out of."

#: 106W017
msgid "Nah, it's too heavy."
msgstr "Nah, it's too heavy."

#: 106W018
msgid "Now what would I use a worn out old truck tire for?"
msgstr "Now what would I use a worn out old truck tire for?"

#: 106W019
msgid "The sheriff loves that tow truck almost as much as he loves his patrol car."
msgstr "The sheriff loves that tow truck almost as much as he loves his patrol car."

#: 106W020
msgid "It's on the other side of the fence!"
msgstr "It's on the other side of the fence!"

#: 106W021
msgid "That stupid mutt has a nasty streak a mile wide! When he was still a puppy, he picked a fight with a lawnmower and chewed it to smithereens! He still has the peg leg to prove it!"
msgstr "That stupid mutt has a nasty streak a mile wide! When he was still a puppy, he picked a fight with a lawnmower and chewed it to smithereens! He still has the peg leg to prove it!"

#: 106W022
msgid "I'm not messing with him. I've seen what those Jaws can do. They just clamp on and never let go."
msgstr "I'm not messing with him. I've seen what those Jaws can do. They just clamp on and never let go."

#: 106W023
msgid "Even though that beast gets fed three times a day, the only thing big enough to hold his food is a truck tire!"
msgstr "Even though that beast gets fed three times a day, the only thing big enough to hold his food is a truck tire!"

#: 106W500
msgid "Oh, what a pain!"
msgstr "Oh, what a pain!"

#: 106W900
msgid "A leather dog collar!"
msgstr "A leather dog collar!"

#: 106W901
msgid "I don't have the dog collar."
msgstr "I don't have the dog collar."

#: 106W902
msgid "That's one powerful winch. I've seen the sheriff impound an 18-wheeler using that thing."
msgstr "That's one powerful winch. I've seen the sheriff impound an 18-wheeler using that thing."

#: 106W903
msgid "A big iron hook!"
msgstr "A big iron hook!"

#: 106W904
msgid "It's on the other side of the fence!"
msgstr "It's on the other side of the fence!"

#: 10N02011
msgid "Coming! Just gotta hold my calls, Gabby. Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, I'll be there in a minute!"
msgstr "Coming! Just gotta hold my calls, Gabby. Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, I'll be there in a minute!"

#: 10N02012
msgid "I hear you, I hear you! Come on, what is this? Get in there! One moment!"
msgstr "I hear you, I hear you! Come on, what is this? Get in there! One moment!"

#: 10N02013
msgid "I'm coming! This place shrink a lot. Straighten this place up, Gabby. We gotta call her. Coming!"
msgstr "I'm coming! This place shrink a lot. Straighten this place up, Gabby. We gotta call her. Coming!"

#: 10N0401
msgid "Wilbur, my boy! What a pleasant surprise! What can I do for you today?"
msgstr "Wilbur, my boy! What a pleasant surprise! What can I do for you today?"

#: 10N0501
msgid "You again? Shouldn't you be out skateboarding or something?"
msgstr "You again? Shouldn't you be out skateboarding or something?"

#: 10N0601
msgid "Look, I'm always happy to talk to my constituents, but this is getting ridiculous. What is it this time?"
msgstr "Look, I'm always happy to talk to my constituents, but this is getting ridiculous. What is it this time?"

#: 10N0701
msgid "Wilbur, how am I supposed to perform my mayoral duties if I spend the whole day yakking it up with you?"
msgstr "Wilbur, how am I supposed to perform my mayoral duties if I spend the whole day yakking it up with you?"

#: 10N0801
msgid "What is it now, Wilbur?"
msgstr "What is it now, Wilbur?"

#: 10N1001
msgid "Well, you're in luck, cuz Help is my middle name! Well, actually, Marion is my middle name, but I'd appreciate it if we kept that between the two of us, if you don't mind."
msgstr "Well, you're in luck, cuz Help is my middle name! Well, actually, Marion is my middle name, but I'd appreciate it if we kept that between the two of us, if you don't mind."

#: 10N1002
msgid "If this is about those space aliens again, I don't want to hear about it."
msgstr "If this is about those space aliens again, I don't want to hear about it."

#: 10N1003
msgid "We're all doing our part, Wilbur. I myself have three recycling bins."
msgstr "We're all doing our part, Wilbur. I myself have three recycling bins."

#: 10N1004
msgid "Hairstyling wax? What the heck are you talking about?"
msgstr "Hairstyling wax? What the heck are you talking about?"

#: 10N1005
msgid "Yep, need some supplies for my animal training business."
msgstr "Yep, need some supplies for my animal training business."

#: 10N1006
msgid "What do you wanna know?"
msgstr "What do you wanna know?"

#: 10N1007
msgid "Oh, isn't that nice? Uh, are you still living with your Aunt Polly?"
msgstr "Oh, isn't that nice? Uh, are you still living with your Aunt Polly?"

#: 10N1008
msgid "Did you decide to get a place of your own?"
msgstr "Did you decide to get a place of your own?"

#: 10N1009
msgid "What you're admiring there is our petunia of peace. It was a bicentennial gift from Boonesville's sister town, Punxsutawney."
msgstr "What you're admiring there is our petunia of peace. It was a bicentennial gift from Boonesville's sister town, Punxsutawney."

#: 10N1010
msgid "Is that right? Well, I suggest you go next door and file a formal complaint."
msgstr "Is that right? Well, I suggest you go next door and file a formal complaint."

#: 10N1011
msgid "Alright, see you later, Wilbur!"
msgstr "Alright, see you later, Wilbur!"

#: 10N1101
msgid "Hamburger meat, you say? Hmm, well, you got one up on me there, Wilbur."
msgstr "Hamburger meat, you say? Hmm, well, you got one up on me there, Wilbur."

#: 10N1201
msgid "Now, why would I have something like that? Styling wax is for sissies, you know!"
msgstr "Now, why would I have something like that? Styling wax is for sissies, you know!"

#: 10N1202
msgid "Look at me! Do I look like someone who needs hair wax? If anything, I need hair!"
msgstr "Look at me! Do I look like someone who needs hair wax? If anything, I need hair!"

#: 10N1203
msgid "Would I lie to you, Wilbert? I'm a politician for crying out loud!"
msgstr "Would I lie to you, Wilbert? I'm a politician for crying out loud!"

#: 10N1204
msgid "With hair like that, you have the gall to tell me that you're desperate? Get out of here, Wilbur! I don't have time for this kind of nonsense."
msgstr "With hair like that, you have the gall to tell me that you're desperate? Get out of here, Wilbur! I don't have time for this kind of nonsense."

#: 10N1205
msgid "I most certainly will."
msgstr "I most certainly will."

#: 10N1301
msgid "Oh yeah, yeah, it's just a part-time thing, but I have trained dogs and cats, ostriches, orangutans, anteaters, crocodiles, heck, you name it, I got it!"
msgstr "Oh yeah, yeah, it's just a part-time thing, but I have trained dogs and cats, ostriches, orangutans, anteaters, crocodiles, heck, you name it, I got it!"

#: 10N1302
msgid "It all started a few years back shortly after the sheriff's bloodhound left us for the great doghouse in the sky. Yep, the sheriff was really sad about losing that dog, so I took it upon myself to train a new animal for him."
msgstr "It all started a few years back shortly after the sheriff's bloodhound left us for the great doghouse in the sky. Yep, the sheriff was really sad about losing that dog, so I took it upon myself to train a new animal for him."

#: 10N1303
msgid "No, no, I didn't give him a bloodhound. I gave him a pig. Of course, by the time I finished training that pig, she could track ascent better than any bloodhound ever could."
msgstr "No, no, I didn't give him a bloodhound. I gave him a pig. Of course, by the time I finished training that pig, she could track ascent better than any bloodhound ever could."

#: 10N1304
msgid "I don't know, maybe it's because you got all that hair hanging down over your eyes. But listen, if you've got any problem critters down at your shop, you just bring them by and let Old Mayor Gus straighten them out for you. For a small service fee, of course."
msgstr "I don't know, maybe it's because you got all that hair hanging down over your eyes. But listen, if you've got any problem critters down at your shop, you just bring them by and let Old Mayor Gus straighten them out for you. For a small service fee, of course."

#: 10N1305
msgid "Don't be a stranger now, Wilbur!"
msgstr "Don't be a stranger now, Wilbur!"

#: 10N1401
msgid "Oh, I don't know about that, but I once trained a German Shepherd to play poker. Now, that was amazing."
msgstr "Oh, I don't know about that, but I once trained a German Shepherd to play poker. Now, that was amazing."

#: 10N1402
msgid "I didn't have a bloodhound, but I did have a pig."
msgstr "I didn't have a bloodhound, but I did have a pig."

#: 10N1403
msgid "I got stuck with it when I foreclosed on a farm."
msgstr "I got stuck with it when I foreclosed on a farm."

#: 10N1404
msgid "No, no, he hated it. Said he didn't want nothing to do with no pig unless it was sizzling on a plate next to his flapjacks at Vera's diner."
msgstr "No, no, he hated it. Said he didn't want nothing to do with no pig unless it was sizzling on a plate next to his flapjacks at Vera's diner."

#: 10N1405
msgid "Well, I sold her to Elmo Perkins. You know, that crazy miner who lives out on the lake? Well, at first I didn't want to sell her. You know, but in the end, I just couldn't refuse all that money the son of a gun was offering me. Never could say no to a quick buck."
msgstr "Well, I sold her to Elmo Perkins. You know, that crazy miner who lives out on the lake? Well, at first I didn't want to sell her. You know, but in the end, I just couldn't refuse all that money the son of a gun was offering me. Never could say no to a quick buck."

#: 10N1406
msgid "He saw her in an animal talent show in the county fair. I buried a sack of apples out in the cornfield, and that pig found him and dug him up in a minute flat. Well, when Elmo saw that, he was instantly convinced that he could use that pig sniffer to find gold in his mine."
msgstr "He saw her in an animal talent show in the county fair. I buried a sack of apples out in the cornfield, and that pig found him and dug him up in a minute flat. Well, when Elmo saw that, he was instantly convinced that he could use that pig sniffer to find gold in his mine."

#: 10N1407
msgid "No, of course not. Don't be silly. Pigs can't smell rocks. I tried to tell him that, but he just wouldn't listen."
msgstr "No, of course not. Don't be silly. Pigs can't smell rocks. I tried to tell him that, but he just wouldn't listen."

#: 10N1408
msgid "Nice talking to you, Wilbur!"
msgstr "Nice talking to you, Wilbur!"

#: 10N1501
msgid "Yep, he had to have that pig no matter what she cost. Yeah, I tell ya, that day I kinda felt like the guy who sold Jack the Magic Beans, you know what I mean?"
