msgid "You should know better than to pester a hungry bork."
msgstr "You should know better than to pester a hungry bork."

#: 512F001B
msgid "Hahaha! How humiliating for you, human!"
msgstr "Hahaha! How humiliating for you, human!"

#: 512F001C
msgid "Nice going, you useless waste of protoplasm!"
msgstr "Nice going, you useless waste of protoplasm!"

#: 512F002A
msgid "What? Were you trying to cook yourself before we turn you into a burger? Crazy!"
msgstr "What? Were you trying to cook yourself before we turn you into a burger? Crazy!"

#: 512F003A
msgid "The Borks have a word for creatures like you, gogobungo. Roughly translated, it means loser!"
msgstr "The Borks have a word for creatures like you, gogobungo. Roughly translated, it means loser!"

#: 512F003B
msgid "Oh, I can hardly wait to smother you with our secret sauce!"
msgstr "Oh, I can hardly wait to smother you with our secret sauce!"

#: 513W001
msgid "Hey, where's my aunt? Is she in there?"
msgstr "Hey, where's my aunt? Is she in there?"

#: 513W002
msgid "Where is she?"
msgstr "Where is she?"

#: 513W003
msgid "Oh, you didn't!"
msgstr "Oh, you didn't!"

#: 513W005
msgid "Oh, you animal!"
msgstr "Oh, you animal!"

#: 513W006
msgid "What? Eating my ant is supposed to make me happy?"
msgstr "What? Eating my ant is supposed to make me happy?"

#: 513Z002
msgid "Easy now. You'll never pass the last test anyway, so what's the difference?"
msgstr "Easy now. You'll never pass the last test anyway, so what's the difference?"

#: 513Z003
msgid "Take heart in the fact that this was a much less painful fate than when I harvest the rest of your planet."
msgstr "Take heart in the fact that this was a much less painful fate than when I harvest the rest of your planet."

#: 513Z004
msgid "Phew! There is just no place in this human."
msgstr "Phew! There is just no place in this human."

#: 513Z005
msgid "Put a break with him!"
msgstr "Put a break with him!"

#: 513Z006
msgid "If this human thinks he knows how to make people happy, then that will be his final test!"
msgstr "If this human thinks he knows how to make people happy, then that will be his final test!"

#: 51N0101
msgid "Shh! Keep it down! I'm on your side!"
msgstr "Shh! Keep it down! I'm on your side!"

#: 51N0102
msgid "The side that's trying to prevent creatures like you from being ground up into burger meat."
msgstr "The side that's trying to prevent creatures like you from being ground up into burger meat."

#: 51N0201
msgid "My name is Astral. I'm a member of the Planet Huggers."
msgstr "My name is Astral. I'm a member of the Planet Huggers."

#: 51N0202
msgid "I mean total bio-extermination. Well, if you fail one of their intelligence tests, you'll see for yourself how awful it is."
msgstr "I mean total bio-extermination. Well, if you fail one of their intelligence tests, you'll see for yourself how awful it is."

#: 51N0203
msgid "Well, aside from getting my jumpsuit completely filthy, I'm spying on Zlark. I'm trying to collect evidence that intelligent lifeforms are being illegally harvested."
msgstr "Well, aside from getting my jumpsuit completely filthy, I'm spying on Zlark. I'm trying to collect evidence that intelligent lifeforms are being illegally harvested."

#: 51N0204
msgid "They have to test you because they aren't supposed to harvest intelligent life forms. Intelligent life is a very scarce resource in the universe."
msgstr "They have to test you because they aren't supposed to harvest intelligent life forms. Intelligent life is a very scarce resource in the universe."

#: 51N0205
msgid "I wouldn't count on it. You don't look all that bright to me."
msgstr "I wouldn't count on it. You don't look all that bright to me."

#: 51N0206
msgid "I was just scanning your DNA for our records. I didn't mean for you to catch me. You weren't moving, so I figured that you had passed out, or that you were dead."
msgstr "I was just scanning your DNA for our records. I didn't mean for you to catch me. You weren't moving, so I figured that you had passed out, or that you were dead."

#: 51N0301
msgid "It's an organization dedicated to the preservation of intelligent life throughout the galaxy. We oppose Orion Burger's barbaric process of planetary destruction. But we meet on the first Thursday of every month."
msgstr "It's an organization dedicated to the preservation of intelligent life throughout the galaxy. We oppose Orion Burger's barbaric process of planetary destruction. But we meet on the first Thursday of every month."

#: 51N0401
msgid "I'm sorry to say that I've seen the protein harvesters perform their ghastly work. Orion Burger wiped out my home planet several years ago, and as far as I know, I'm the only survivor."
msgstr "I'm sorry to say that I've seen the protein harvesters perform their ghastly work. Orion Burger wiped out my home planet several years ago, and as far as I know, I'm the only survivor."

#: 51N0501
msgid "You got that right. I'm a stowaway. Oh, if Zlark found out I was here, I'd be history. Whatever you do, don't let him know that I'm here."
msgstr "You got that right. I'm a stowaway. Oh, if Zlark found out I was here, I'd be history. Whatever you do, don't let him know that I'm here."

#: 51N0701
msgid "The tests aren't supposed to hurt."
msgstr "The tests aren't supposed to hurt."

#: 51N0801
msgid "Come on, look around out there. Not many survive their neuroanalysis test."
msgstr "Come on, look around out there. Not many survive their neuroanalysis test."

#: 51N0901
msgid "Quickly, get away from the vent. And remember, you never saw me."
msgstr "Quickly, get away from the vent. And remember, you never saw me."

#: 51P0102
msgid "Uh, exactly what side would that be?"
msgstr "Uh, exactly what side would that be?"

#: 51P0103
msgid "Oh, well, that definitely sounds like the side that I'm on."
msgstr "Oh, well, that definitely sounds like the side that I'm on."

#: 51P0201
msgid "Who are you?"
msgstr "Who are you?"

#: 51P0202
msgid "What do you mean exactly by planetary destruction?"
msgstr "What do you mean exactly by planetary destruction?"

#: 51P0203
msgid "What are you doing in the ventilation duct?"
msgstr "What are you doing in the ventilation duct?"

#: 51P0204
msgid "Why the IQ tests? Why don't they just eat me?"
msgstr "Why the IQ tests? Why don't they just eat me?"

#: 51P0205
msgid "What are my chances for passing these tests?"
msgstr "What are my chances for passing these tests?"

#: 51P0206
msgid "What was that thing you were waving in my face?"
msgstr "What was that thing you were waving in my face?"

#: 51P0301
msgid "What are planet huggers?"
msgstr "What are planet huggers?"

#: 51P0402
msgid "That's terrible! And now they're planning to do the same thing to my planet!"
msgstr "That's terrible! And now they're planning to do the same thing to my planet!"

#: 51P0403
msgid "Just when I thought my life couldn't get any worse, now I'm not even at the top of the food chain anymore."
msgstr "Just when I thought my life couldn't get any worse, now I'm not even at the top of the food chain anymore."

#: 51P0501
msgid "So, you're sneaking around through this ship, and those green guys don't even know that you're in here?"
msgstr "So, you're sneaking around through this ship, and those green guys don't even know that you're in here?"

#: 51P0601
msgid "Yeah, I've noticed."
msgstr "Yeah, I've noticed."

#: 51P0701
msgid "Hey, I'll have you know that if they can stand the screaming, I can stand the pain."
msgstr "Hey, I'll have you know that if they can stand the screaming, I can stand the pain."

#: 51P0702
msgid "Those bozos were just zapping my head with electricity! It didn't exactly tickle."
msgstr "Those bozos were just zapping my head with electricity! It didn't exactly tickle."

#: 51P0801
msgid "Dead!"
msgstr "Dead!"

#: 51P0802
msgid "Hmm, I see what you mean."
msgstr "Hmm, I see what you mean."

#: 51P0901
msgid "Uh-oh! I think I hear someone coming!"
msgstr "Uh-oh! I think I hear someone coming!"

#: 52N0101
msgid "How do you know my name? And how did you know I was in here?"
msgstr "How do you know my name? And how did you know I was in here?"

#: 52N0102
msgid "A time warp?"
msgstr "A time warp?"

#: 52N0103
msgid "Oh, well, I was monkeying around with the neutrino pulse gun controls a little while ago, but I didn't think it would cause a time warp to happen. Hmm, fascinating."
msgstr "Oh, well, I was monkeying around with the neutrino pulse gun controls a little while ago, but I didn't think it would cause a time warp to happen. Hmm, fascinating."

#: 52N0201
msgid "What for?"
msgstr "What for?"

#: 52N0202
msgid "Cage? You humans live in cages?"
msgstr "Cage? You humans live in cages?"

#: 52N0203
msgid "The Planet Huggers will use it to generate bad publicity for Orion Burger. We might even be able to put them out of business!"
msgstr "The Planet Huggers will use it to generate bad publicity for Orion Burger. We might even be able to put them out of business!"

#: 52N0204
msgid "Mutants? Do they have laser guns?"
msgstr "Mutants? Do they have laser guns?"

#: 52N0205
msgid "Knowing Zlark, the ray gun he gave you is probably barely powerful enough to defrost his lunch."
msgstr "Knowing Zlark, the ray gun he gave you is probably barely powerful enough to defrost his lunch."

#: 52N0206
msgid "They home in on life signs. Perhaps you could run around quickly and confuse their targeting systems and get them to zap each other."
msgstr "They home in on life signs. Perhaps you could run around quickly and confuse their targeting systems and get them to zap each other."

#: 52N0207
msgid "No problem. But just remember, don't let them find out that you're in a time warp."
msgstr "No problem. But just remember, don't let them find out that you're in a time warp."

#: 52N0301
msgid "Oh, well, you're very welcome."
msgstr "Oh, well, you're very welcome."

#: 52N0401
msgid "Oh, well, in that case, Zlarg is already cheating. This is just the sort of evidence I was hoping to collect. His test scenarios are supposed to reflect your natural habitat."
msgstr "Oh, well, in that case, Zlarg is already cheating. This is just the sort of evidence I was hoping to collect. His test scenarios are supposed to reflect your natural habitat."

#: 52N0501
msgid "Hmm... clearly you'll have to eliminate these mutant gerbils before escape from the cage is possible."
msgstr "Hmm... clearly you'll have to eliminate these mutant gerbils before escape from the cage is possible."

#: 52N0601
msgid "It sounds to me as if the only thing in that case that can destroy the mutant gerbils are the mutant gerbils themselves."
msgstr "It sounds to me as if the only thing in that case that can destroy the mutant gerbils are the mutant gerbils themselves."

#: 52P0101
msgid "Psst, OSTRO!"
msgstr "Psst, OSTRO!"

#: 52P0102
msgid "I've talked with you before. I'm in some kind of time warp. I've been reliving the day over and over again."
msgstr "I've talked with you before. I'm in some kind of time warp. I've been reliving the day over and over again."

#: 52P0103
msgid "It has something to do with that abductotron machine. I think there was some kind of malfunction."
msgstr "It has something to do with that abductotron machine. I think there was some kind of malfunction."

#: 52P0201
msgid "Thanks a lot!"
msgstr "Thanks a lot!"

#: 52P0202
msgid "I can't figure out how to escape from the cage!"
msgstr "I can't figure out how to escape from the cage!"

#: 52P0203
msgid "What do you plan to do with this evidence?"
msgstr "What do you plan to do with this evidence?"

#: 52P0204
msgid "Speaking of gerbils, those mutants are trying to kill me!"
msgstr "Speaking of gerbils, those mutants are trying to kill me!"

#: 52P0205
msgid "Zlar gave me a ray gun too."
msgstr "Zlar gave me a ray gun too."

#: 52P0206
msgid "How can I get them to destroy each other?"
msgstr "How can I get them to destroy each other?"

#: 52P0207
msgid "Thanks for the advice!"
msgstr "Thanks for the advice!"

#: 52P0301
msgid "You brought me some extra time to pass these crazy tests. Actually, an infinite amount of time."
msgstr "You brought me some extra time to pass these crazy tests. Actually, an infinite amount of time."

#: 52P0401
msgid "Of course not!"
msgstr "Of course not!"

#: 52P0402
msgid "I can assure you, that cage is my gerbil's natural habitat, not mine."
msgstr "I can assure you, that cage is my gerbil's natural habitat, not mine."

#: 52P0501
msgid "Yeah, big ones!"
msgstr "Yeah, big ones!"

#: 52P0601
msgid "It is pretty cheesy."
msgstr "It is pretty cheesy."

#: 53N0102
msgid "I wouldn't expect a lot of courtesy from them, especially not from Zlarg. Every time you pass one of his tests, you're delaying his harvest. Ha! I'll bet that you're really starting to try what little patience he has."
msgstr "I wouldn't expect a lot of courtesy from them, especially not from Zlarg. Every time you pass one of his tests, you're delaying his harvest. Ha! I'll bet that you're really starting to try what little patience he has."

#: 53N0103
msgid "He eats. He eats all the time. It's no wonder those gluttons need such a huge supply of protein for their restaurants."
msgstr "He eats. He eats all the time. It's no wonder those gluttons need such a huge supply of protein for their restaurants."

#: 53N0104
msgid "That's the spirit!"
msgstr "That's the spirit!"

#: 53P0101
msgid "Ow! Watch it, you bubble-blowing buffoon!"
msgstr "Ow! Watch it, you bubble-blowing buffoon!"

#: 53P0102
msgid "Oh, I wish those aliens would treat their guests with a little more courtesy."
msgstr "Oh, I wish those aliens would treat their guests with a little more courtesy."

#: 53P0103
msgid "Poor guy... uh, by the way, what does he do while I'm working on one of his tests?"
msgstr "Poor guy... uh, by the way, what does he do while I'm working on one of his tests?"

#: 53P0104
msgid "Well, glutton or not, he's not getting his tentacles on any of my protein."
msgstr "Well, glutton or not, he's not getting his tentacles on any of my protein."

#: 53P0105
msgid "Uh, I hear someone coming. I'll talk to you later."
msgstr "Uh, I hear someone coming. I'll talk to you later."

#: 54N0101
msgid "Is that so?"
msgstr "Is that so?"

#: 54N0102
msgid "An Orion burger. Ugh. Well, that shouldn't be so hard to find. Just follow its disgusting smell."
msgstr "An Orion burger. Ugh. Well, that shouldn't be so hard to find. Just follow its disgusting smell."

#: 54N0201
msgid "Ugh, you actually put one of those things in your mouth?"
msgstr "Ugh, you actually put one of those things in your mouth?"

#: 54N0202
msgid "Really? I can practically smell the stench of one of those things through the void of space."
msgstr "Really? I can practically smell the stench of one of those things through the void of space."

#: 54N0203
msgid "Well, if your nose can't track an intensely pungent burger, chances are your other senses aren't particularly strong either. Maybe you should try to amplify them somehow."
msgstr "Well, if your nose can't track an intensely pungent burger, chances are your other senses aren't particularly strong either. Maybe you should try to amplify them somehow."

#: 54N0401
msgid "That's too bad. Sounds like you have a bit of a problem, then. We are talking about a test of your sensory perception, after all."
msgstr "That's too bad. Sounds like you have a bit of a problem, then. We are talking about a test of your sensory perception, after all."

#: 54P0101
msgid "Man, that sensory test is really hard!"
msgstr "Man, that sensory test is really hard!"

#: 54P0102
msgid "Yeah, it's some kind of treasure hunt. I'm supposed to find a hidden Orion burger."
msgstr "Yeah, it's some kind of treasure hunt. I'm supposed to find a hidden Orion burger."

#: 54P0201
msgid "It smells disgusting, but it tastes even worse!"
msgstr "It smells disgusting, but it tastes even worse!"

#: 54P0202
msgid "I can't follow the burger's smell. It's too far away."
msgstr "I can't follow the burger's smell. It's too far away."

#: 54P0203
msgid "Do you have any other suggestions?"
msgstr "Do you have any other suggestions?"

#: 54P0301
msgid "Zlar didn't exactly give me a choice in the matter."
msgstr "Zlar didn't exactly give me a choice in the matter."

#: 54P0401
msgid "I guess my nose isn't as sensitive as yours."
msgstr "I guess my nose isn't as sensitive as yours."

#: 54P0501
msgid "Amplify my senses. I'll have to give that some thought."
msgstr "Amplify my senses. I'll have to give that some thought."

#: 55N0101
msgid "You passed another test!"
msgstr "You passed another test!"

#: 55N0102
msgid "Sorry. Hey, who knows? Maybe there is hope for you earthlings this time after all."
msgstr "Sorry. Hey, who knows? Maybe there is hope for you earthlings this time after all."

#: 55N0103
msgid "Well, according to our records, Orion Burger harvested your planet once before, some 50 million years ago."
msgstr "Well, according to our records, Orion Burger harvested your planet once before, some 50 million years ago."

#: 55N0104
msgid "The protein harvesters must have accidentally left behind enough genetic material to allow life to re-establish itself."
msgstr "The protein harvesters must have accidentally left behind enough genetic material to allow life to re-establish itself."

#: 55P0102
msgid "Yeah. Well, you don't have to act so surprised about it."
msgstr "Yeah. Well, you don't have to act so surprised about it."

#: 55P0103
msgid "This time? What do you mean, this time?"
msgstr "This time? What do you mean, this time?"

#: 55P0104
msgid "50 million years ago? Oh, man! You mean to say that the dinosaurs disappeared because they were made into Orion burgers?"
msgstr "50 million years ago? Oh, man! You mean to say that the dinosaurs disappeared because they were made into Orion burgers?"

#: 55P0105
msgid "So that's what Zlarg meant when he said that the Earth was a second-growth planet. Beautiful! I think I need to lie down for a minute."
msgstr "So that's what Zlarg meant when he said that the Earth was a second-growth planet. Beautiful! I think I need to lie down for a minute."

#: 56N0101
msgid "What's the problem?"
msgstr "What's the problem?"

#: 56N0102
msgid "Could you be a little more specific? I mean, what do they look like?"
msgstr "Could you be a little more specific? I mean, what do they look like?"

#: 56N0103
msgid "Borks? Oh, no! Those are nasty little pets!"
msgstr "Borks? Oh, no! Those are nasty little pets!"

#: 56N0201
msgid "I'll say. I once had one eat a hole right through the hull of my spaceship while I was trying to maneuver my way through an asteroid belt. I was fortunate to get out of that unpleasant situation in one piece."
msgstr "I'll say. I once had one eat a hole right through the hull of my spaceship while I was trying to maneuver my way through an asteroid belt. I was fortunate to get out of that unpleasant situation in one piece."

#: 56N0202
msgid "Hmm, I'm not surprised. You're obviously going to have to learn a little Borkese so that you can decipher these instructions."
msgstr "Hmm, I'm not surprised. You're obviously going to have to learn a little Borkese so that you can decipher these instructions."

#: 56N0203
msgid "No, I don't. But I'm sure their language is relatively simple. They are pretty mindless creatures after all."
msgstr "No, I don't. But I'm sure their language is relatively simple. They are pretty mindless creatures after all."

#: 56N0204
msgid "Well, when I'm visiting a foreign planet and I need to pick up the local lingo, I'll often watch what people are doing and listen to what they're saying. That way I can associate their words with their actions, which allows me to build up a rough working knowledge of the language fairly quickly."
msgstr "Well, when I'm visiting a foreign planet and I need to pick up the local lingo, I'll often watch what people are doing and listen to what they're saying. That way I can associate their words with their actions, which allows me to build up a rough working knowledge of the language fairly quickly."

#: 56N0205
msgid "Did they give you a gizmo with rainbow colored buttons?"
msgstr "Did they give you a gizmo with rainbow colored buttons?"

#: 56N0206
msgid "Give me a break. I'm having a really bad hair day. It just loses all of its body in these damp ventilation ducts."
msgstr "Give me a break. I'm having a really bad hair day. It just loses all of its body in these damp ventilation ducts."

#: 56N0207
msgid "See you later!"
msgstr "See you later!"

#: 56N0401
msgid "And you just told me that the borax will rainbow color too."
msgstr "And you just told me that the borax will rainbow color too."

#: 56N0501
msgid "I hate these undercover assignments. At least I remember to bring my mirror along with me this time."
msgstr "I hate these undercover assignments. At least I remember to bring my mirror along with me this time."

#: 56P0101
msgid "Psst! Astral, I'm having a bit of trouble with this language test."
msgstr "Psst! Astral, I'm having a bit of trouble with this language test."

#: 56P0102
msgid "Well, I have to exterminate a bunch of weird little space critters."
msgstr "Well, I have to exterminate a bunch of weird little space critters."

#: 56P0103
msgid "Well, they're fat, and rainbow-colored, and all they ever seem to do is eat and destroy things. Zlarg called them __________?"
msgstr "Well, they're fat, and rainbow-colored, and all they ever seem to do is eat and destroy things. Zlarg called them __________?"

#: 56P0201
msgid "You're familiar with books?"
msgstr "You're familiar with books?"

#: 56P0202
msgid "The extermination instructions I was given are in bork ease."
msgstr "The extermination instructions I was given are in bork ease."

#: 56P0203
msgid "Do you know how to speak, Borkies?"
msgstr "Do you know how to speak, Borkies?"

#: 56P0204
msgid "How am I ever going to learn to speak Borkese?"
msgstr "How am I ever going to learn to speak Borkese?"

#: 56P0205
msgid "How will I know which instruction to use for each block?"
msgstr "How will I know which instruction to use for each block?"

#: 56P0206
msgid "You sure spend a lot of time fussing with your hair."
msgstr "You sure spend a lot of time fussing with your hair."

#: 56P0207
msgid "I better get going. I don't want to get caught talking to you."
msgstr "I better get going. I don't want to get caught talking to you."

#: 56P0301
msgid "You know? That's so crazy, it just might work!"
msgstr "You know? That's so crazy, it just might work!"

#: 56P0401
msgid "Yeah?"
msgstr "Yeah?"

#: 56P0402
msgid "Yeah? Oh, of course! The buttons are color-coded! Boy, is my face red."
msgstr "Yeah? Oh, of course! The buttons are color-coded! Boy, is my face red."

#: 56P0501
msgid "That's awful. I wouldn't want your hair to be all limp when my planet gets harvested."
msgstr "That's awful. I wouldn't want your hair to be all limp when my planet gets harvested."

#: 57N0101
msgid "Yes, I know. I witnessed the whole thing. It was awful. I'm so sorry."
msgstr "Yes, I know. I witnessed the whole thing. It was awful. I'm so sorry."

#: 57N0201
msgid "Come on, Wilbur. You can't afford to get all emotional right now. You have to pull yourself together for the logic test."
msgstr "Come on, Wilbur. You can't afford to get all emotional right now. You have to pull yourself together for the logic test."

#: 57N0202
msgid "The bigger they are, the harder they fall."
msgstr "The bigger they are, the harder they fall."

#: 57N0203
msgid "You can't give up, Wilbur. Zlard may have eaten your ant, but you can still stop him from harvesting the rest of your planet."
msgstr "You can't give up, Wilbur. Zlard may have eaten your ant, but you can still stop him from harvesting the rest of your planet."

#: 57N0204
msgid "If you pass, your planet becomes a fully sanctioned intergalactic refuge for developing intelligent lifeforms. As such, Zlarg would have no choice but to call off the harvest."
msgstr "If you pass, your planet becomes a fully sanctioned intergalactic refuge for developing intelligent lifeforms. As such, Zlarg would have no choice but to call off the harvest."

#: 57N0205
msgid "Okay, Wilbur."
msgstr "Okay, Wilbur."

#: 57N0401
msgid "That's the spirit. Besides, you are almost there. The logic test is the last one."
msgstr "That's the spirit. Besides, you are almost there. The logic test is the last one."

#: 57N0501
msgid "True, but he knows that the planet huggers are watching. He won't take that chance."
msgstr "True, but he knows that the planet huggers are watching. He won't take that chance."

#: 57P0101
msgid "That big green animal just ate my Aunt Polly!"
msgstr "That big green animal just ate my Aunt Polly!"

#: 57P0201
msgid "Why did he have to drag my Aunt Polly into this?"
msgstr "Why did he have to drag my Aunt Polly into this?"

#: 57P0202
msgid "Oh, Zlarg is gonna pay for this!"
msgstr "Oh, Zlarg is gonna pay for this!"

#: 57P0203
msgid "What do I do now? These tests are hopeless!"
msgstr "What do I do now? These tests are hopeless!"

#: 57P0204
msgid "What happens if I pass this last test?"
msgstr "What happens if I pass this last test?"

#: 57P0205
msgid "I'll talk to you later. I have to collect my thoughts."
msgstr "I'll talk to you later. I have to collect my thoughts."

#: 57P0301
msgid "Yeah? Well, then Zlar's gonna fall awfully hard!"
msgstr "Yeah? Well, then Zlar's gonna fall awfully hard!"

#: 57P0401
msgid "Yeah, you're right. I'll pass these stupid tests... somehow."
msgstr "Yeah, you're right. I'll pass these stupid tests... somehow."

#: 57P0402
msgid "HALLELUJAH!"
msgstr "HALLELUJAH!"

#: 57P0501
msgid "What? Zlarg call off the harvest? I wouldn't trust that big blowhard any further than I could throw him!"
msgstr "What? Zlarg call off the harvest? I wouldn't trust that big blowhard any further than I could throw him!"

#: 57P0502
msgid "Ha! If he only knew how closely you're watching him!"
msgstr "Ha! If he only knew how closely you're watching him!"

#: 58N0101
msgid "What is it now?"
msgstr "What is it now?"

#: 58N0102
msgid "Make people happy? Well, sounds like you have your work cut out for you. I mean, no offense, but you humans do get a little over-emotional at times and..."
msgstr "Make people happy? Well, sounds like you have your work cut out for you. I mean, no offense, but you humans do get a little over-emotional at times and..."

#: 58N0103
msgid "See what I mean? In any event, I don't think that I can help you this time. You know a lot more about humans than I do."
msgstr "See what I mean? In any event, I don't think that I can help you this time. You know a lot more about humans than I do."

#: 58N0104
msgid "Look, now that's not very logical either."
msgstr "Look, now that's not very logical either."

#: 58P0101
msgid "Psst. ASTRO!"
msgstr "Psst. ASTRO!"

#: 58P0102
msgid "I could really use some help with this crazy logic test. I have to figure out how to make a bunch of people happy."
msgstr "I could really use some help with this crazy logic test. I have to figure out how to make a bunch of people happy."

#: 58P0103
msgid "Astro, are you gonna help me out or what?"
msgstr "Astro, are you gonna help me out or what?"

#: 58P0104
msgid "I suppose you're right. Well, at least wish me luck."
msgstr "I suppose you're right. Well, at least wish me luck."

#: 58P0105
msgid "Oh, never mind. Uh-oh, I hear someone coming!"
msgstr "Oh, never mind. Uh-oh, I hear someone coming!"

#: 600W001
msgid "Wow! My very own space blaster!"
msgstr "Wow! My very own space blaster!"

#: 600W002
msgid "These ray guns seem much more powerful on TV."
msgstr "These ray guns seem much more powerful on TV."

#: 600W003
msgid "I'd better not."
msgstr "I'd better not."

#: 600W004
msgid "Nah, why bother?"
msgstr "Nah, why bother?"

#: 600W005
msgid "I couldn't do that!"
msgstr "I couldn't do that!"

