#: 92N0701
msgid "I miss those days. So you see, Eugene does have a good side."
msgstr "I miss those days. So you see, Eugene does have a good side."

#: 92N0702
msgid "Yeah, right."
msgstr "Yeah, right."

#: 92N0703
msgid "Hey, watch it, Beanpole! I got a cleaver back here!"
msgstr "Hey, watch it, Beanpole! I got a cleaver back here!"

#: 92N0801
msgid "Oh, that! Yeah, it was that stupid sheriff! He'd come in here every single day, plunk a couple hours worth of quarters in the machine, and fall asleep! Listen to that same sappy song over and over and over!"
msgstr "Oh, that! Yeah, it was that stupid sheriff! He'd come in here every single day, plunk a couple hours worth of quarters in the machine, and fall asleep! Listen to that same sappy song over and over and over!"

#: 92N0802
msgid "I think he gets the idea, Eugene."
msgstr "I think he gets the idea, Eugene."

#: 92N0901
msgid "It was just some silly country song. All the sheriff ever listens to is country music."
msgstr "It was just some silly country song. All the sheriff ever listens to is country music."

#: 92N0902
msgid "Yeah, every single day. In the booth over by the door. It was genuinely comical. Country music puts him out like a lot."
msgstr "Yeah, every single day. In the booth over by the door. It was genuinely comical. Country music puts him out like a lot."

#: 92N0903
msgid "That country music was driving me nuts! I had to break them! Either that or I was going to stick my head in the oven!"
msgstr "That country music was driving me nuts! I had to break them! Either that or I was going to stick my head in the oven!"

#: 92N0904
msgid "We tried that, but the sheriff had just waked up and plugged it back in again. It seems the country music kept him asleep. It was like a lullaby for him."
msgstr "We tried that, but the sheriff had just waked up and plugged it back in again. It seems the country music kept him asleep. It was like a lullaby for him."

#: 92N0905
